VergilBench corpus — provenance + licenses

The corpus is 100 contracts. License posture: permissive only — no
GPL / AGPL / BUSL anywhere in `vergilbench/`. Two provenance tiers:

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
TIER 1 — Vergil-authored seed (10 contracts, Apache-2.0)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Single-file simplifications conformant with their reference standards:

* erc20, erc20-capped, erc20-pausable → ERC-20 family
* erc721 → ERC-721
* vault-4626 → ERC-4626
* amm-constant-product → Uniswap-V2-style pair, inlined accounting
  (NOT derived from Uniswap source — Uniswap V2 is GPL-3.0, V3 is BUSL)
* lending → Compound-style surface, simplified semantics
* ownable-counter, simple-multisig, timelock-release → common patterns

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
TIER 2 — Real-world OpenZeppelin (90 contracts, MIT) — Slice A8
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Source:   OpenZeppelin Contracts
Version:  v5.1.0
Commit:   69c8def5f222ff96f2b5beff05dfba996368aa79
License:  MIT (see vergilbench/vendor/openzeppelin-contracts-5.1.0/LICENSE)

The OZ library is vendored verbatim (mocks/ pruned) under
`vergilbench/vendor/openzeppelin-contracts-5.1.0/` and resolved by each
corpus entry via foundry `allow_paths` + `@openzeppelin/contracts/`
remappings. Every `oz-*` corpus entry is a minimal concrete deployment
over the real OZ implementation — the shape the OZ Contracts Wizard
generates and that teams actually ship. The contract logic under test is
unmodified OZ code; the only Vergil-authored parts are the thin concrete
wrapper, the `Properties.t.sol` harness, and `properties.yaml`.

A small number of entries layer a thin Vergil-authored override on real
OZ bases to capture common deployment patterns OZ does not ship directly
(soulbound transfer-block, compliance blocklist, anti-whale max-wallet,
fee-on-transfer, capped-supply drop, deposit-capped 4626). These are
clearly named and documented as "pattern over OZ" rather than verbatim OZ.

Families covered: ERC-20 (+ Burnable / Capped / Pausable / Permit /
Votes / FlashMint / Wrapper / 4626 / combinations), ERC-721 (+ Burnable /
Enumerable / Pausable / Royalty / URIStorage / Wrapper / Consecutive /
Votes / combinations), ERC-1155 (+ Supply / Burnable / Pausable /
URIStorage / combinations), access control (Ownable / Ownable2Step /
AccessControl / + Enumerable / + DefaultAdminRules / AccessManager),
finance (VestingWallet / + Cliff), governance (TimelockController),
proxies/upgradeability (ERC1967 / UUPS / Transparent / Beacon / Clones),
metatx (ERC2771Context), and utility/crypto/struct libraries (Pausable /
ReentrancyGuard / Nonces / EnumerableSet / EnumerableMap / BitMaps /
DoubleEndedQueue / Checkpoints / Math / SafeCast / SignedMath / ECDSA /
MerkleProof / EIP712 / MessageHashUtils / SignatureChecker / Create2 /
StorageSlot / Multicall / Strings / Base64 / ShortStrings / Comparators /
ERC165 / ERC165Checker / ERC2981).

solc: entries pin 0.8.20, except the proxy entries (oz-erc1967-proxy,
oz-uups, oz-transparent-proxy) which pin 0.8.28 — ERC1967Utils requires
^0.8.21 and 0.8.21 itself has a Natspec internal-compiler bug.

Excluded on license grounds (publicly accessible but NOT permissive):
Uniswap V2 (GPL-3.0), Uniswap V3 / parts of Aave (BUSL-1.1), Solmate
(AGPL-3.0). These do not appear anywhere in `vergilbench/`.
